The evidence with the title 'Time after time: Mandatory overtime in the U.S. economy ... ' says Jan 1, 2002  ... The Fair Labor Standards Act Of 1938 ( FLSA ) , which regulates overtime , currently imposes no limits on overtime hours , nor does it prohibit dismissaloranyother ... . Indeed, the public health considerations associated with long work hours suggest that excessive overtime hours should be legally capped. 
